        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 12:43AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 1243 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Badin Lake to 10 miles northeast of
Ansonville. Movement was northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Troy, Badin Lake, Biscoe, Badin, Denton, Mount Gilead, Star, Uwharrie
Haven, Eldorado, and Fish Tales Marina.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
